<TITLE> Court hears appeal to remand Tarique on Dec 2 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  The Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court for Dhaka Tuesday set Dec 2 for hearing an appeal to remand Tarique Rahman in custody for questioning in a corruption case. The investigation officer of the case petitioned to the court of additional chief metropolitan magistrate Md Golam Rabbani to remand the elder son of former prime minister Khaleda Zia for seven days. The assistant director of the Anticorruption Commission, Md Toufiqul Islam, filed the petition before the Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. The court has sent Tarique into remand for a total of 10 days in four extortion cases although he is yet to be questioned. The investigation officer in the remand appeal said Tarique needed to be questioned about the source of money deposited in Prime Bank and Dhaka Bank, ownership of Basundhara Group (block no 1064) and the Daily Dinkal, which he mentioned in his wealth statement to the ACC. ACC deputy director Md Zahirul Huda filed the case with Kafrul Police Station against Tarique, his wife Zobaida Rahman and mother-in-law Syeda Iqbalmand Banu on Sept 26. bdnews24.c
